L2: Professional INTRO
L3: SHELAGH ABATE is an internationally renowned horn player and educator with a passion for pushing boundaries and making music that transcends genres. For over 25 years Shelagh has been firmly established herself as a leading figure in the demanding New York freelance world and beyond with versatile artistry in the classical contemporary commercial and jazz idioms.  In any given week Shelagh can be found in a Broadway pit orchestra soundtrack recording and onstage with legendary pop icons.
L4: 
L5: Educational Intro
L6: As an educator Shelagh’s style is  dynamic educator her style is dynamic enthusiastic and authentic. She believes that the best teachers are those that never stop learning and that the best lessons can come from the most unexpected places.  Shelagh brings enthusiasm authenticity and a genuine desire to learn new things with her wherever she teaches.  This infectious curiosity shines through to any student in any environment from private lessons to chamber music to the entire symphony orchestra.  into the room with her She maintains an insatiable desire to continue learning remaining curious; as Tthe best teachers know that they are always in a position to grow and that working with students is a learning experience for the student and the teacher.   at least as much as they have to share with others.
L7: 
L8: Broadway Meat
L9: **What does opening a broadway show mean?
L10: **Emphasize the versatility of the shows - Fiddler SP and MM were traditional 1950’s schlocky playing.  Anastasia Poppins and Frozen were disney screamers and GG and Honeymoon were weird off the wall.  
L11: Honeymoon won a Tony
L12: Any other show accolades?
L13: Name drop the big ones Wicked POTO LK etc. you did LK in Boston so include it.  Big names = good.  
L14: Shelagh has opened more than one dozen Broadway productions. Mary Poppins A Gentleman’s Guide to Love and Murder South Pacific Honeymoon in Vegas Evita Fiddler on the Roof Anastasia Disney’s Frozen and The Music Man with Hugh Jackman at the Wintergarden Theater. to name a few. 
L15: Commercial Meat
L16: Shelagh has established fluency in the commercial realm as well as the classical having performed as part of the Lincoln Center Jazz Orchestra with Wynton Marsalis Michel Legrand the ensembles of Earl McDonald Gary Morgan Jamie Baum John Allmark The Gil Evans Project with Ryan Truesdell John Vanore and Greg Hopkins. Shelagh has recorded performed live in concert as well as on televised events with Sting The Who Tony Bennett Rufus Wainwright Lady Gaga Barry Manilow Joni Mitchell Trey Anastasio Club d’Elf Josh Groban Brian Wilson Linda Ronstadt and on Tony Awards at Radio City Music Hall. 
L17: 
L18: Recording meat
L19: Innumerable television commercials video game soundtracks and motion picture soundtracks feature Shelagh's ensemble playing as well. - Movie soundtracks / name drop composers (Danny Elfman etc).  
L20: Name drop NFL NHL etc.  Definitely use Clash of Clans!!!!!
L21: 
L22: PIVOT - Classical meat
L23: Since arriving in New York in 2005 sShelagh has performed regularly with The Metropolitan Opera Orchestra The Mostly Mozart Festival The American Ballet Theater The American Symphony Orchestra The Opera Orchestra of New York and is “staff?  What do they call it when it’s your gig?  In house?  IDK Shelagh is (tenured?) is third horn with the Greenwich Symphony Orchestra and has been principal horn of the Vermont Symphony Orchestra under the artistic direction of Jaime Laredo since 1999. 
L24: During the course of her career she has been conducted by some of the great musicians of our time; Seiji Ozawa Simon Rattle Andre Previn James Conlon Gunther Schuller James DePriest Robert Spano Carl St. Clair John Williams Marin Alsop Jaime Laredo Keith Lockhart and Placido Domingo among others.s.
L25: 
L26: Shelagh has established fluency in the commercial realm as well as the classical having performed as part of the Lincoln Center Jazz Orchestra with Wynton Marsalis Michel Legrand the ensembles of Earl McDonald Gary Morgan Jamie Baum John Allmark The Gil Evans Project with Ryan Truesdell John Vanore and Greg Hopkins. Shelagh has recorded performed live in concert as well as on televised events with Sting The Who Tony Bennett Rufus Wainwright Lady Gaga Barry Manilow Joni Mitchell Trey Anastasio Club d’Elf Josh Groban Brian Wilson Linda Ronstadt and on Tony Awards at Radio City Music Hall. Innumerable television commercials video game soundtracks and motion picture soundtracks feature Shelagh's ensemble playing as well.
L27: 
L28: Chamber Meat
L29: Chamber music has been at the very core of Shelagh’s success as a musician. A winner of the Coleman Competition (2000) and a founding member of the award-winning Triton Brass (Fischoff Lyon & Concert Artist’s Guild 2005) Shelagh has collaborated with her world-class and longtime colleagues in order to achieve what is only artistically possible through such an intimate medium. Together they have shared their gifts with many thousands of others through live performances recordings and education. 
L30: 
L31: Academic Meat
L32: Abate is a committed educator who prides herself on being authentic sharing her dedication to expressing one’s own voice through their instrument whatever it may be. She joined the faculty of the Berklee College of Music ( https://college.berklee.edu/brass/faculty/shelagh-abate )as Assistant Professor of Horn in 2022 after lecturing and serving as adjunct in various capacities all over the United States. She has also been a proud faculty member of the Boston University Tanglewood Institute in Lenox MA ( https://www.bu.edu/cfa/tanglewood/faculty-artists/faculty/) since 2003. Shelagh has led countless seminars masterclasses and clinics at High Schools Colleges and Universities on a regular basis since completing her graduate studies in 2001. 
L33: 
L34: Shelagh’s early musical influences include extensive study with the Boston Symphony Orchestra’s Richard Sebring Toronto Symphony’s principal horn Neil Deland and renowned pedagogue and performer Laura Klock. She has been a fellow at the Tanglewood Music Center and with The National Repertory Orchestra. Shelagh holds a B.A. from Boston College an M.M. from The University of Massachusetts at Amherst where she was a recipient of the Howard W. Lebow Scholarship and an Artist Diploma from The New England Conservatory of Music where she was a Walkenier Scholar. Shelagh is proud to be a Stephens Horns artist playing one of the very first horns handcrafted by Stephen Shires https://www.stephenshorns.com.

Based on the document you provided, here's a concise resume for Shelagh Abate:

---

**Shelagh Abate**
*Internationally Renowned Horn Player & Educator*

**Professional Experience:**
- Over 25 years in the New York freelance scene, showcasing versatile artistry in classical, contemporary, commercial, and jazz idioms.
- Regular performances in Broadway orchestras, soundtrack recordings, and concerts with legendary pop icons.

**Education:**
- B.A. from Boston College
- M.M. from The University of Massachusetts, Amherst (Howard W. Lebow Scholarship recipient)
- Artist Diploma from The New England Conservatory of Music (Walkenier Scholar)

**Broadway Highlights:**
- Opened over a dozen Broadway productions including "Mary Poppins," "A Gentleman’s Guide to Love and Murder," "South Pacific," "Anastasia," "Disney’s Frozen," and "The Music Man" with Hugh Jackman.

**Commercial & Recording Experience:**
- Performed with Lincoln Center Jazz Orchestra, Wynton Marsalis, and other notable artists.
- Recorded and performed live with Sting, The Who, Tony Bennett, Lady Gaga, and more.
- Featured in numerous television commercials, video game soundtracks, and motion picture soundtracks.

**Classical Engagements:**
- Regular performances with The Metropolitan Opera Orchestra, The Mostly Mozart Festival, and others.
- Third horn with the Greenwich Symphony Orchestra.
- Principal horn of the Vermont Symphony Orchestra since 1999.

**Chamber Music:**
- Winner of the Coleman Competition (2000).
- Founding member of the award-winning Triton Brass.

**Academic Roles:**
- Assistant Professor of Horn, Berklee College of Music (since 2022).
- Faculty member, Boston University Tanglewood Institute (since 2003).
- Regularly conducts seminars, masterclasses, and clinics.

**Early Musical Influences:**
- Extensive study with renowned musicians and educators.

**Recognition:**
- Stephens Horns artist, playing handcrafted horns by Stephen Shires.

---
